description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CARE COORDINATOR Band 4 1 position x 37.5 Hours &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PERMANENT CONTRACT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly self-motivated and enthusiastic individual with exceptional administration and IT skills to join our team of Care Co-ordinators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Care Co-ordinator you will be based in a local cluster of general practices and community teams in the Dudley Borough, where you will play a lead role in co-ordinating support for the most vulnerable patients in the community to help them access health and social care services and the necessary support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to use your own initiative and be able to work unsupervised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have the ability to communicate effectively and utilise IT and research skills in order to provide accurate and timely patient information from a number of sources. You will work closely with GP’s and their practice teams and other professionals, as part of a wider multi agency integrated team approach to managing care, playing a pivotal role in the effective running of multi-disciplinary meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact: Kate Keeling 01384 323133 for any further information you may require.&lt;/p&gt;
